Motorists are being urged to drive with caution on the N17 and N2 in Mpumalanga amid another truck blockade. The N17 between Warburton and Ermelo and the N2 between Mkhondo and Ermelo in Mpumalanga has been partially closed by truck drivers protesting over the employment of foreign nationals. Police are monitoring the situation. There have been a number of similar incidents on other highways in recent months including on the N3. Mpumalanga Community Safety spokesperson Moeti Musi has advised motorists to be extra cautious if driving on the N17 and N2. 